fetchit (1.3.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add comprehensive GitHub Actions CI/CD workflow for automated releases
  * Implement multi-platform release bundling (Linux amd64/arm64, Windows x64/x86)
  * Generate Debian packages for Ubuntu and Debian distributions
  * Cross-architecture build support with proper binary naming
  * Add Windows MSVC build support (Makefile.vc enhancements)
  * Improve .gitignore to exclude build artifacts and dist files
  * Update copyright year to 2024-2026
  * Streamline build system for cleaner release process

 -- Keira Hopkins <open-source@keirahopkins.co.uk>  Tue, 15 Apr 2026 18:08:00 +0100

fetchit (1.3.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Major performance improvements reducing execution time by ~90%
  * Removed threading overhead that was causing futex bottlenecks
  * Optimised file I/O operations and reduced syscall count
  * Enhanced CPU frequency detection with reliable fallback methods
  * Eliminated duplicate memory info file reads
  * Improved GPU detection with pattern matching instead of directory scanning
  * Optimised package counting to avoid expensive directory traversal
  * Added multi-filesystem storage display showing all important mount points
  * Build system optimisations with aggressive compiler flags

 -- Keira Hopkins <open-source@keirahopkins.co.uk>  Sun, 31 Aug 2025 22:54:00 +0100

